	   <a name=103890520057296></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103890520057296><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=103890520057296>Spec Reccomendation</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=103890520057296#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=186606><span id= >Pire</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>2 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Dec 3rd 4:10 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>For all you low level mages out there, no matter how tempting it may seem, do *NOT* specialize in evocation.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a 60th level mage who was once specialized in evocation, I can safely say from experience that evocation is vastly inferior to conjuration.  Nearly all of the high level nukes with the exception of rains and bolts (which really aren't used very much) are all conjure based.  Additionally, all of the pet summons, and more importantly, item summons are conjure.  Finally, and perhaps the most convincing reason of all, is that with maxed out conjure, a mage can get infinite mana by using a few skills.  With Summoning Efficiency 3(focus), Improved Reclaim Energy(AA), Elemental Pact(AA), and maxed out Spec: Conjure(Skill), a mage can continually summon and reclaim his pet and regain mana very quickly in the process.  Hope this helps someone out.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
