	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103996398844147><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=103996398844147>RE: Spec Reccomendation</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=103996398844147#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=73372><span id=Sage>Malaclypse</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>114 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Dec 15th 10:17 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>To answer your question, in the temple of Solusek Ro, there's a NPC named Ostrom. If you give him a ruby and 50gp he'll reset your specializations. Not sure if the 50gp is needed, but he asks for it.<br><br>Once you leave the temple all your specializations will be reduced to 49. If they were lower than that they won't get bumped up. Anyway, then just practice conjuration till it hits 51, then you're locked in. <br><br>And Pire is right. At the endgame almost all the spells that you'll be casting are conjuration based. Our best nukes, pets, summons, etc.<br><br>You can get by with evocation though, and until you start getting quite high level, you will almost be better off. As you progress, your nukes tend to go evocation, conjuration, evocation, conuration... up through the spell sets. But once you get past 55 it really just makes more sense to have it in conjure.<br><br><br><br>Faelawen Starfyre, the Mad Mage of Povar<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
