	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Dec 15th 10:40 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.75]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ahh the call of the treasure hunter. Well for starters I'd reccomend browsing around this fine site for info. Generally speaking at 28 you're going to have a pretty hard time hunting for stuff. I'd reccomend doing quests rather than attempting to camp things. If you can get groups you might try evil eyes in beholder's, and runnyeye has some decent loot. Bring company though. I've done the occasional crawl through there at 50+ just for the hell of it, and it can get nasty. Frigging gobbies backstab for 200+.<br><br>&quot;You have been hit for 5 damage. You have been hit for 7 damage. You have been backstabbed for 176 damage.&quot;<br><br>Me: What the hell???<br><br>you get the idea.<br><br>Unrest has some decent stuff in it, Najena has a couple ok items, but the time will come when you're going to have to live there for epic parts, so you'll see pretty much everything that drops there.<br><br>It's really hard to say, most of the nice items are hard to get till you're 40+<br><br>That being said you can still make a lot of cash.<br>I made 200k at level 25 just by doing item trading in Gfey. That was back before the bazaar was open though, and things are considerably different now.<br><br>However those differences can be taken advantage of. What you need to keep in mind is that high level players need items for tradeskills that you are the PERFECT level to camp. And we're willing to pay through the nose for em too.<br><br>Heady Kiolas and spider silk for tailoring sell for about 5pp and 2pp respectively. (Prices from Povar. Your milage may vary) That's 100pp and 40pp per stack for something that takes maybe 30 mins to get. There are a lot of other things like that too. Iron Oxides are rare as hell and drop off of low level mobs in steamfront. It's not uncommon to see those go for 500 to 1000 each. that's each. Or to put it another way, 10k to 20k a stack. That being said though, they're hard as hell to get. My wife (in game and hopefully soon to be out of game) has been camping em on and off for over a month. She's found 3 of em. They spawn on the ground but VERY rarely. Mostly they drop off of elementals. Anyway, that's an option but keep in mind you'll be there for such a damn long time you're almost better off just making kiolas.<br><br>There are a lot of other components tradeskillers will pay for. But that gives you an idea. It's probably the quickest and safest way to make cash at low levels. Boring as hell, but it brings in the plat.<br><br>Once ya have that, you can buy yer phat lewtz.<br><br><br><br>Faelawen Starfyre, the Mad Mage of Povar, 55th season, former merchant and best equipped 21 mage ever, leader of Defiant Heroes, arch nemesis of the evil squirrel empire, et al.<br><br>&quot;Greed, for lack of a better term, is good.&quot; <br>-Gordon Gecko, Wallstreet<br><br>PS: incidentally, if you're feeling masochistic and want to try the iron oxides, they drop off earth elementals and (RARELY!!!) spawn on the ground in place of russet oxide. They also drop from the fire elementals in lavastorm, and sol A and B, as well as the fire and earth elementals in najena. They also drop with fair regularity in the Hole, but that's a 50+ zone so I doubt you'll be hunting there for a bit. heh.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sun Dec 15 10:22:24 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
