	   <a name=103759161066769></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103759161066769><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=103759161066769>RE: Magician and Races</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=103759161066769#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=73372><span id=Sage>Malaclypse</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>114 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Nov 17th 11:15 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.75]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Being totally honest, there isn't really that big a difference toward the end of the game. A high level mage is going to be powerful regardless of what race you pick.<br><br>That being said, at the VERY start you'll probably have an easier time of it as either a high elf or a gnome. They both start in fairly good newbie areas and orc belts can be turned in at kaladim for good exp up to lvl 16ish.<br><br>Humans are good, but suffer from being damn near blind at night, and have a pretty low starting int. Dark elves have ultra vision, but are an evil race, so be prepared for a LOT of faction work.<br><br>Erudites have good starting int, but are as nightblind as humans and start in probably the worst newbie area in the game.<br><br>Elves and Gnomes are the most popular mage classes, on povar at least.<br><br>However, like I said, as you start gaining levels, race doesn't really matter too much. Stats are more dependant on equip, and with POP and Luclin out, it's easy enough to get around at low levels to the point where you're no longer stuck in a single newbie area till you level up enough to travel. I wouldn't worry about it. Just go for the Role Play value.<br><br><br><br>Faelawen Starfyre, the Mad Mage of Povar<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sun Dec 15 10:26:39 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
