	   <a name=10366928089039></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10366928089039><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=10366928089039>RE: Levels</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=10366928089039#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=189264><span id=Scholar>Lord Barmodius</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>19 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Nov 7th 1:34 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>West, East, and North Karana are all great XP and great loot, but you need to have easy access to a bank to drop off the heavy pelts and the SoL expansion.<br><br>Getting from lvl 10 to lvl 15 in the Karanas (erudite mage), I made over 800pp, and that is with keeping quite a bit of stuff.<br><br>Take a small sewing kit, and a skinning knife if you can find it.&nbsp;&nbsp;If your tailoring sucks, take a stack of patterns.  Then start killing every bear, lion, wolf, spiderling, and Giant spider you can find.  For the spiderlings, use the sewing kit, combine and get silk threads, and stack 'em.  For spiders, do the same for swatches.  This will get your skill up for the big moneymaker later, and these can be sold for obscene amounts of money.  <br><br>Keep the ruined pelts for wolves, bears, and cats.  When your trivial for silk hits its limit, use the patterns and the ruined pets and make patchwork leather armor til it maxes.  You can sell this to merchants for about a 5sp profit.  Then use the patterns with some of the silk swatches to make raw silk armor.  You can wear this if you are a caster/monk and not already twinked.  You can also sell this to merchants for a 3gp profit per item.  Max out with that, and you're ready for big bucks.  Stack the HQ pelts and grin merrily at each one you get because these are easy money.  Stack the MQ and LQ pelts also.  Everything else (except the ultra-rare thick grizzly skin) is garbage.<br><br>Now, take any LQ pelts and combine them with silk threads for leather padding, the greatest money maker for lowbies.  This stuff is 20-50pp EACH depending on your server.  Take any MQ pelts and combine them with the skinning knife (get at bazaar or from a smith) to make LQ pelts, and repeat.<br><br>Make sure you have full stacks of silk, silk threads, swatches, HQ pelts, and padding, and go to NK and ride the spires to Luclin.  Buy a bag or two in the bazaar, get the current prices and set up as a trader, then go AFK and go to sleep or go to work/school.  By the time you return, you'll have a whole heap of platinum where those stinking heavy hides used to be.  Buy yourself something nice, then repeat as necessary.<br><br>In the meantime, you'll have leveled a couple times and not even noticed it.  Skills will be up, and buying the next tier of spells will be easy.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
