	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103587325642578><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=103587325642578>RE: Solo...</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=103587325642578#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=73372><span id=Sage>Malaclypse</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>114 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Oct 29th 1:53 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.70]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Actually yeah, Air pet stuns will prevent the mob from acting for 3.1 seconds (Pet LVL.1) to 5.9 seconds (Pet LVL.42). Pets higher than 42 will still only have the stun last 5.9 seconds max. Now, I believe, and correct me if I'm wrong, that stun duration can be reduced depending on the mob's resists, but 5.9 is the max.<br><br>Now the reason air pets are so damn good against casters is that the stun interrupts spells REGARDLESS OF IF IT LANDS. <br><br>In other words, even if the mob can still take action, whatever spell it is casting will be interrupted. That's how killing Lady Vox works, stun as much as possible and hope it interrupts her CH, even though she'll still be attacking.<br><br><br><br>-Fael<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
